This executive order, issued on August 28, 2017, by President Donald J. Trump, revokes Executive Order 13688, which was issued on January 16, 2015. The order also revokes the recommendations issued in accordance with Executive Order 13688, stating that they do not reflect the policy of the executive branch. All executive departments and agencies are directed to cease implementing these recommendations and take prompt action to rescind any rules, regulations, guidelines, or policies that were implementing them. The order does not affect the authority granted by law to executive departments or agencies, nor does it affect the functions of the Director of the Office of Management and Budget. The order should be implemented consistent with applicable law and subject to the availability of appropriations. It is important to note that this order does not create any right or benefit, substantive or procedural, enforceable by any party against the United States or any other person.